								"path": "Basic Set/Basic Set Traits.adq",
								"id": "tUl2tCfZVgRF9QWYx"
							},
							"name": "Pacifism: Cannot Kill",
							"reference": "B148",
							"local_notes": "You may fight – you may even start fights – but you may never do anything that seems likely to kill another. This includes abandoning a wounded foe to die “on his own”! You must do your best to keep your companions from killing, too. If you do kill someone (or feel responsible for a death), you immediately suffer a nervous breakdown. Roll 3d and be totally morose and useless for that many days. During this time, you must make a Will roll to offer any sort of violence toward anyone, for any reason.",
